  m_Name: Forepaw_Digit2_Phalanx_R
  m_EditorClassIdentifier: Assembly-CSharp::ModelPartDataSO
  id: Forepaw_Digit2_Phalanx_R
  partName: Forepaw Digit2 Phalanx Right
  descriptionChunks:
  - The right forepaw digit two phalanx is a skeletal bone forming part of the second
    digit within the canine forepaw. This structure supports toe movement, stability,
    and proper paw mechanics during locomotion.
  - Tendons and ligaments attached to the phalanx enable controlled flexion and extension
    necessary for balanced movement and weight distribution. The digit contributes
    to traction, coordination, and shock absorption while the paw contacts the ground
    during walking or running.
